  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "Reduced physical accessibility and connectivity for the people living in the remote areas of Nepal has resulted in a high incidence of poverty, which contribute to income disparity and social discrimination with respect to their access to public services. While Nepal till recently made impressive gains in the field of trail bridge building, the re-organisation of the government structures has led to dispersement of the trained human resources.  The newly established local and State governments lack institutional and technical capacities to implement Trail Bridges building programme."
    },
